    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="bibliography" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
                    <p>
                        <bibl><ptr target="#IDodoneDVC"/> <citedRange>186A+187A+190B</citedRange></bibl> (<bibl><ptr target="MéndezDosuna2016"/>, <citedRange>120-121</citedRange> </bibl> [<bibl><ptr target="SEG"/> <citedRange>66.461</citedRange>]; </bibl><bibl><ptr target="MéndezDosuna2018b"/>, <citedRange>290</citedRange></bibl>; <bibl><ptr target="#CIOD"/> <citedRange> 190B+186A+187A</citedRange> [last consulted 25/06/2026]</bibl>).
                         </p>
                    <p>
                      Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#AlonsoDéniz2022"/>, <citedRange>444 n. 17</citedRange> (on the alphabet)</bibl>;
                        <bibl><ptr target="#AnagnostopoulouGalaniMenti2022"/>, <citedRange>243 n. 16 and 245 n. 24</citedRange> (on oracular questions about professional activity).</bibl>
                    </p>
            </div>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="grc">
            <div type="textpart" subtype="face" n="B">
                        <ab>                   
                    <lb n="1"/>γᾶν Ϝοικε͂ι πότερα  
                     <lb n="2"/>ἐν Ὀπόεντι 
                    </ab>
  
                </div>
                <div type="textpart" subtype="face" n="A">
                    <ab>
                        <lb n="1"/> καὶ ἐν Ὀρχομενο͂ι 
                        <lb n="2"/> καὶ hόπαι κα νο͂ς φέρι;   
                         </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
                <app loc="l. 4">
      <rdg resp="#IDodoneDVC"><supplied reason="omitted">ἱ</supplied>κανο͂ς φέρει</rdg>
      <rdg resp="#MéndezDosuna2018b #CIOD">κα νο͂ς φέρι</rdg></app>
</div>
            <div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
                <p>Whether he/she should settle in Opous, or in Orchomenos, or wherever his/her mind leads him/her.</p>
                </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="es">
                <p>¿Debe residir en Opunte, o en Orcómeno o donde su mente lo/la lleve?</p>
                
                </div>
            <div type="commentary" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en"> 
                <p>The three inscriptions, edited separately by <bibl><ptr target="#IDodoneDVC"/></bibl>, are written in the same hand and belong to the same enquiry. <bibl><ptr target="#MéndezDosuna2016"/></bibl> proposed joining the two inscriptions on side A (186A and 187A), following Tsantsanoglou’s suggestion in the editio princeps. In 2022, Lhôte and Carbon (<foreign xml:lang="la">apud</foreign> <bibl><ptr target="#CIOD"/></bibl>) added inscription 190B, incised on the other side, which thus constitutes the beginning of the anonymous oracular enquiry. </p>
                
<p>According to these scholars, the inscription is written in a Northwestern Doric dialect using the local alphabet of Dodona, whereas the first editors identified it with Boeotian or Thessalian alphabet. However, the shape of the digamma is indicative of a non-Dodonaean origin (see <bibl><ptr target="#AlonsoDéniz2022"/></bibl>), and the adverb <foreign xml:lang="grc">hόπαι</foreign> appears to point towards Boeotian (see <bibl><ptr target="#MéndezDosuna2018b"/></bibl>).</p>
                
                <p n="Ithaca Results">Ithaca attributes the inscription to Epirus with a high degree of confidence both when the reading of the first editors is adopted for l. 4 (88.41%) and when Méndez Dosuna’s correction is accepted (87.77%). In both cases, the model dates the inscription to the 5th century BC, with the highest probability assigned to the beginning of the century (410-400 BC; 13.53% and 12.77%, respectively), followed closely by the middle (12.41% and 12.40%) and the end (12.76% and 11.89%) of the same century. See Test 1 <ref target="https://dodonaonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/IDodoneOnline186A_187A_190B_Test1_2026_06_30.html">Ithaca results</ref> and <ref target="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/IDodone/IDodoneOnline/refs/heads/main/ithaca-results/IDodoneOnline186A_187A_190B_Test1.md">metadata</ref>, and a snapshot of the <ref target="https://dodonaonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/IDodoneOnline186A_187A_190B_Test1_geographical-attribution_2026_06.jpg">geographical attribution</ref>; Test 2 <ref target="https://dodonaonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/IDodoneOnline186A_187A_190B_Test2_2026_06_30.html">Ithaca results</ref> and <ref target="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/IDodone/IDodoneOnline/refs/heads/main/ithaca-results/IDodoneOnline186A_187A_190B_Test2.md">metadata</ref>, and a snapshot of the <ref target="https://dodonaonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/IDodoneOnline186A_187A_190B_Test2_geographical-attribution_2026_06.jpg">geographical attribution</ref>.</p>
         </div>
